SIMPLE: subsumption
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Subsumption
<hw>Sub*sump"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
act of subsuming, or of including under another.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The first act of consciousness was a <qex>subsumption</qex> of
that of which we were conscious under this notion.</q> <rj><qau>Sir W.
Hamilton.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>That which is subsumed, as the minor clause or
premise of a syllogism.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>But whether you see cause to go against the rule, or the
<qex>subsumption</qex> under the rule.</q> <rj><qau>De
Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Subsumptive</ent>⟦br⟧
